@startuml Cocro API — REST & WebSocket

skinparam defaultFontName Courier
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam ParticipantPadding 20

' ============================================================
' ACTORS / PARTICIPANTS
' ============================================================
actor       "Client (mobile/web)"  as C
participant "Spring Security\n(JWT filter)"  as SEC
participant "AuthController\n/auth"          as AUTH
participant "GridController\n/api/grids"     as GRID
participant "SessionController\n/api/sessions" as SC
participant "SessionWebSocketController\n/ws (STOMP)" as WSC
participant "StompAuthChannelInterceptor"    as INT
participant "Use Cases"                      as UC
participant "MongoDB"                        as DB
participant "Redis\n(grid state cache)"      as REDIS

' ============================================================
' 1. AUTHENTICATION
' ============================================================
== Authentication ==

C  -> AUTH : POST /auth/register\n{ username, password }
AUTH -> DB  : save User
AUTH --> C  : 201 { token, userId, username, roles }

C  -> AUTH : POST /auth/login\n{ username, password }
AUTH -> DB  : load + verify password
AUTH --> C  : 200 { token, userId, username, roles }

C  -> AUTH : POST /auth/guest
AUTH -> DB  : create anonymous User\n(generated username, ANONYMOUS role)
AUTH --> C  : 201 { token, userId, username, roles }

note right of C
  All subsequent REST calls include:
  Authorization: Bearer <token>
end note

' ============================================================
' 2. GRID MANAGEMENT
' ============================================================
== Grid Management ==

C  -> SEC  : POST /api/grids\n{ gridShareCode, sizeX, sizeY, cells, clues }
SEC -> GRID : authenticated
GRID -> DB  : persist Grid
GRID --> C  : 200 { gridId }

C  -> SEC  : PATCH /api/grids\n{ gridShareCode, cells, clues }
SEC -> GRID : authenticated
GRID -> DB  : update Grid
GRID --> C  : 200

' ============================================================
' 3. SESSION LIFECYCLE — REST
' ============================================================
== Session Lifecycle (REST) ==

C  -> SEC  : POST /api/sessions\n{ gridId }
SEC -> SC  : authenticated
SC -> UC   : CreateSessionUseCase
UC -> DB   : persist Session (status=CREATING)
UC --> SC  : Success { shareCode }
SC --> C   : 201 { shareCode }

C  -> SEC  : POST /api/sessions/join\n{ shareCode }
SEC -> SC  : authenticated
SC -> UC   : JoinSessionUseCase
UC -> DB   : add Participant (status=JOINED)
UC --> SC  : Success { participantCount }
SC --> C   : 200 { shareCode, participantCount }\nor 409 SessionFull / AlreadyParticipant

C  -> SEC  : POST /api/sessions/start\n{ shareCode }
SEC -> SC  : authenticated (creator only)
SC -> UC   : StartSessionUseCase
UC -> DB   : set Session.status = PLAYING
UC --> SC  : Success
SC --> C   : 200\nor 400 NotCreator / InvalidStatusForAction

C  -> SEC  : POST /api/sessions/leave\n{ shareCode }
SEC -> SC  : authenticated
SC -> UC   : LeaveSessionUseCase
UC -> DB   : set Participant.status = LEFT
UC --> SC  : Success
SC --> C   : 200

note right of C
  Grid updates are WebSocket-only.
  See "WebSocket — Grid Update" below.
end note

C  -> SEC  : GET /api/sessions/{shareCode}/state
SEC -> SC  : authenticated
SC -> UC   : GetSessionStateUseCase
UC -> REDIS: get cached SessionGridState\n(fallback → MongoDB)
UC --> SC  : SessionGridStateDto
SC --> C   : 200 { revision, cells[] }

' ============================================================
' 4. WEBSOCKET / STOMP
' ============================================================
== WebSocket / STOMP Connection ==

C  -> WSC  : WS handshake  ws://<host>/ws
C  -> INT  : STOMP CONNECT\n{ Authorization: Bearer <token>,\n  shareCode: <code> }
INT -> INT : validate JWT\nstore CocroAuthentication\n+ shareCode in session attributes
INT --> C  : STOMP CONNECTED

note right of INT
  StompAuthChannelInterceptor (ExecutorChannelInterceptor)
  - preSend()     → validates JWT on CONNECT (Tomcat thread)
  - beforeHandle()→ restores auth to SecurityContextHolder
                    on executor thread for each SEND/SUBSCRIBE
  - afterMessageHandled() → clears SecurityContextHolder
end note

== WebSocket — Welcome ==

C  -> WSC  : SUBSCRIBE /app/session/{shareCode}/welcome
WSC -> DB  : load Session
WSC -> REDIS: get cached grid revision
WSC --> C  : SessionWelcome {\n  shareCode, topicToSubscribe,\n  participantCount, status,\n  gridRevision }

note right of C
  Client then subscribes to:
  /topic/session/{shareCode}
  to receive all broadcast events.
end note

== WebSocket — Grid Update ==

C  -> WSC  : SEND /app/session/{shareCode}/grid\n{ posX, posY, commandType, letter? }
WSC -> UC  : UpdateSessionGridUseCase
UC -> REDIS: CAS update (revision++)
UC -> WSC  : broadcast GridUpdated event
WSC --> C  : broadcast to /topic/session/{shareCode}\nGridUpdated { actorId, posX, posY,\n  commandType, letter }

note right of REDIS
  On CAS conflict:
  StompSessionNotifier sends private
  SyncRequired { currentRevision }
  to the lagging client via:
  /user/queue/session
end note

== WebSocket — Broadcast Events ==

note over WSC
  All broadcasts to /topic/session/{shareCode}:

  ParticipantJoined  { userId, participantCount }
  ParticipantLeft    { userId, participantCount, reason }
  SessionStarted     { participantCount }
  GridUpdated        { actorId, posX, posY, commandType, letter }

  Private to user (/user/queue/session):
  SessionWelcome     (via @SubscribeMapping)
  SyncRequired       { currentRevision }
end note

' ============================================================
' 5. BACKGROUND SCHEDULERS
' ============================================================
== Background Schedulers ==

note over REDIS, DB
  HeartbeatTimeoutScheduler (every 15s)
    For each tracked participant:
      if lastHeartbeat > 30s ago → LeaveSessionUseCase (reason=timeout)
      broadcasts ParticipantLeft { reason: "timeout" }

  SessionFlushScheduler (every 30s)
    For each idle SessionGridState in Redis:
      flush updated state to MongoDB
end note

@enduml
